IT’S A WRAP FOR ARTBOX 2023 AND I CANNOT BELIEVE WE MANAGED TO PULL OFF THIS 🔥 EVENT!!! I had such a hard time picking just 10 photos but here are my favourites (bonus last photo that features my ratchet drawing of the Beam of Pain when it existed only in my head 8 months ago haha)

ARTBOX is honestly a crazy dream come true for me because I’ve always wanted to bring @sgagsg’s brand of cheekiness to a physical stage! I remember standing on stage one of the evenings, looking at the huge crowd and went “wow, is this really happening??”

So I really want to say THANK YOU to all of you who came down to @artbox_singapore to support us! Seeing you guys having a blast, laughing while watching people suffer on the Beam of Pain as well as the ridiculous National Shake Leg & Paper Toss Championships were really the highlights for me! HAHAHA! It was really amazing to meet so many of you face to face finally too!

A big big shoutout to all my amazing friends, fellow creators in the media industry, clients, partners and investors for coming down to support too! I really appreciate you guys taking the time to give our event a little stardust!! 

And of course, thank you to @kentxteo and the rest of the @invade.co team for allowing us to be co-organiser of your baby! I hope we didn’t disappoint!!! 

The BIGGEST SHOUTOUT goes to my entire @sgagsg fam definitely; the people who took care of design, programmes, hosts, casts, creators, tech, photos, content, sponsorship, BD, accounts and finance. Together with our awesome part-timers, you guys are truly the heroes behind the amazing success we had at ARTBOX!! I know some of you guys have the videos of me embarrassingly in tears as I gave my thank you speech on the last night but I genuinely meant every word that I said from the bottom of my heart 🥲

Last but not least, thank you to le wife for coming down to ARTBOX every single day with ploop ploop just to show your moral support! Thank you for also tanking all the baby-caring duties while I was so absorbed with the planning and running of the event! YOU ARE AMAZING ✨✨

See you guys at next year’s ARTBOX maybe? Hahaha! Idk let me catch up on some sleep first then we see how!

When I first took the Puffing Billy many years ago, it was such an amazing experience that I told myself that if I ever have kids of my own, I’ll bring them here. Today, my dream came true 🥹

Anyway tips for people headed to Puffing Billy:
- Try to come 45-60 min before your scheduled departure time to get in the queue early
- Sit on the right side of the train to catch the really nice “cross the bridge” shot
- Standby your phone once the train starts moving off cause the bridge is less than a min away
- Bring some food along so you wouldn’t have to queue for so-so only food at only restaurant at Lakeside
